FG-541 — Limited-Record Guard (Stay Inside the Mandate)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: On return, police the scope—no new facts beyond the mandate.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote mandate task/time/scope; move to disregard beyond-scope pages; offer tiny alternative (≤3-page letters on scope only).
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft an 8-line “beyond scope” notice with two pins to the mandate text.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Mandate limits findings to (a–d) (Op. p.3). Disregard S-2 pp.3–4 (outside scope); alternatively letters ≤3 pp in 7/7 days.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Scope discipline = credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A boundary box around “Task (a–d)” with stray pages flagged “Out.”

⸻

FG-542 — Remand ICS Calendar (Owners • Alerts • Roll-Forward)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put remand dates into calendars with owners and alerts.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ICS rows: Task • Due • Owner • Alerts (7/3/1d); include local time; roll forward weekends/holidays.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export an ICS for findings/status/OA window and share with all counsel.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings 09/15 — Owner Court — Alerts 7/3/1d; Status 09/22 — Owner Appellant.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Calendars make promises real.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A calendar tile showing three bell icons (7/3/1).

⸻

FG-543 — Two-Page Return Reply (Fit Only, No Flourish)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Answer what changed on remand—nothing more.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ¶1: mandate line + findings pins; ¶2: gap (if any) + relief; footer “No new facts.”
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a ≤2-page return reply with four pins and a two-line order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings at Dkt 101:2–3; Tab 3 p.2. Gap remains (harm not reached) → remand 21d or clarify n.3.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Fit persuades; volume distracts.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two tight paragraphs feeding a mini order strip.

⸻

FG-544 — 902(11) Declaration Template (Self-Auth in One Page)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Authenticate business records once, reuse everywhere.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Elements: custodian identity, kept in ordinary course, timely made, source/method reliability; attach hash for digital.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 1-page 902(11) template with blank fields for file name, date, and hash.
	•	✅ Model Response: “I am custodian… ‘USPS_Receipt.jpg’ kept in ordinary course… SHA-256 9f2a….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Provenance before payload.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A short sworn form with a fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-545 — “Pin First” Findings Sheet (Write What You Want Signed)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Offer one-line findings with pin blanks the court can adopt.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Four lines: Success/Harm/Equities/Public; checkbox Reached/Not reached; pin placeholder; neutral verbs only.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build the sheet and attach to your return packet.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm: ‘Record shows timing loss’ (____). □ Reached □ Not reached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: The easiest line to sign is the one you wrote.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A checklist with empty pin boxes.

⸻

FG-546 — “Decide by Date” Return Notice (Clock + Fallback)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: After remand, ask for a decision by [date] with a tiny fallback.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One paragraph: why the date (calendar pin), two findings pins, relief line, fallback admin stay 48–72h if not ready.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line “decide by” notice with a small stay fallback.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Please decide by 09/30 (vendor cutover). Pins: Dkt 101:2–3; Tab 3 p.2. Relief: decide or admin stay ¶3 72h.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Dates + pins move calendars.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A date chip with a tiny pause ribbon.

⸻

FG-547 — Third-Party Burden Objection (Vendors/Agencies Not Bound)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Protect innocents with a burden objection + carve-out.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One sentence: order binds parties only; no obligations on non-party vendors/agencies; propose reporting instead of restraint.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-line burden objection for your order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “No obligations on non-party vendors; order binds parties only; weekly vendor attestation suffices.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Narrow scopes survive appeal.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A bracketed paragraph with a “vendors carved out” tag.

⸻

FG-548 — Compliance Declaration (What • When • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Convert progress into sworn proof.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Bullets: step done, date/time, artifact pin; end with perjury line; keep ≤1 page; hash if posted.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 9-line compliance decl. with two exhibit pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “09/12 redesign shipped (Ex A:1); 09/14 testing complete (Ex B:1). I declare….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Process logs become leverage.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A sworn page with two receipt thumbnails.

⸻

FG-549 — Finding-to-Order Map (Each Line → Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show how each finding supports the exact order text.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Finding line • Pin • Order snippet; keep ≤1 page; cite once in the return letter.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 6-row map linking findings to the two-line order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm found — Dkt 101:2 — Decide now; Harm not reached — Tab 3 p.2 — Remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Mapping converts pages to signatures.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A three-column strip with arrows to a mini order card.

⸻

FG-550 — Public Closeout Note (Docs • Hashes • Next)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: End remand publicly: what happened • hashes • next.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 90–120 words: date, findings outcome, two hashed links (findings/status), and the next date (decision/clarify window).
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your public note and add it to the case page.
	•	✅ Model Response: “09/22—Findings entered (Dkt 101:2–3; sha …); Return status filed (sha …). Next: decision request by 09/30.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Public memory pressures action.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small web card with two fingerprinted links and a calendar ch